   31: Then `mean(Δ_w)=+0.49` says “distributed wins,” while `(ΣD-ΣC)/ΣO=-1/101≈-0.0099` says “central wins.” `E[(D-C)/O]`, `E[D-C]/E[O]`, and `median((D-C)/O)` are different estimands, not interchangeable summaries.
